{
  "texts": [
    "Under this strategy, all timestamps within an anomalous segment are assigned the highest anomaly score present within that segment, thus the whole anomaly segment is considered to be detected if at least one anomaly score surpasses the threshold.",
    "Then the F1 score is obtained in a point-based manner (point-wise PA in Fig. 4).",
    "Anomaly Weights Revision.",
    "However, the naive point-wise PA introduces biased true positives and false negatives.",
    "As shown in Fig. 4, as a long anomaly segment is detected under point-adjustment, even if two false alarms are triggered, the Precision is up to 0.8, which contradicts the demand corresponding to issue b."
  ]
}